==English==

===Pronunciation===
* {{audio|en-us-alloy.ogg|Audio (US)}}
* {{IPA|/ˈalɔɪ/}}

===Etymology 1===
From {{etyl|xno|en}} {{term|alai|lang=fro}}, from {{etyl|fro|en}} {{term|aloi|lang=fro}}, from {{term|aloiier|lang=fro}}.

====Noun====
{{en-noun}}

# A [[metal]] that is a combination of two or more [[element]]s, at least one of which is a metal.
# An [[admixture]]; something added which [[stain]]s, [[taint]]s etc.
#* '''1603''', {{w|John Florio}}, translating Michel de Montaigne, ''Essays'', II.20:
#*: ''Metrodorus'' said that in sadnesse there is some '''aloy''' of pleasure.

