===Etymology 2===
From {{etyl|fro|en}} {{term|aloiier||assemble, join|lang=fro}}, from {{etyl|la|en}} {{term|alligare||bind to, tie to|lang=la}}, compound of {{term|ad||to|lang=la}} + {{term|ligare||to bind|lang=la}}.

====Verb====
{{en-verb}}

# To [[mix]] or combine; often used of metals.
# To reduce the purity of by mixing with a less valuable substance.
#: ''to '''alloy''' gold with silver or copper, or silver with copper''
# {{context|figurative|lang=en}} To [[impair]] or [[debase]] by mixture.
#: ''to '''alloy''' pleasure with misfortunes''

